.TH B64
.SH NAME
b64 /- Base64 encoder/decoder operating on streams
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B b64
[\fB\-e\fR] 
[\fB\-d\fR \fIASCII\fR \fIbinary\fR]
[\fB\-i\fR \fIinput_stream\fR]
[\fB\-o\fR \fIoutput_stream\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B b64
by default takes input from stdin and transcodes it to stdout, though streams
may be specified using the options. Base64 may be decoded to ASCII formatted
characters or to a binary stream.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-e
Encode input stream to Base64 on output stream.
.TP
.BR \-d " " \fIASCII\fR  \fIbinary\fR
Decode input stream to either ASCII formatted characters or to binary.
.TP
.BR \-i " " \fIinput_stream\fR
Specify input stream or file.
.TP
.BR \-o " " \foutput_stream\fR
Specify output stream or file.
